Package team_gold_zork

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Character  
    Command
    This class takes in a command from the user and executes it.
    CommandFactory
    This Singleton class parses a command from a user and creates a Command object for it.
    DropCommand
    Deals with commands that drop an object.
    Dungeon
    This class allows for the storage and creation of rooms in a dungeon.
    Event
    This class deals with events that are triggered by commands, which are related to specific objects or characters.
    Exit
    This class stores all the exits in a Room.
    GameConfig
    This class stores all static fields which remain constant throughout the game.
    GameState
    This class stores the current location and dungeon of the player.
    HealthCommand
    Deals with a user's request to print out the player's health.
    Interpreter
    This class creates a dungeon and prompts the player for commands.
    InventoryCommand
    Deals with commands to view a player's inventory.
    Item
    This class stores attributes for an item contained within a dungeon
    ItemSpecificCommand
    Deals with commands that can only be performed on certain objects.
    MovementCommand  
    Player  
    Room
    This class allows for the creation and storage of rooms.
    SaveCommand  
    ScoreCommand
    Deals with commands to view a player's score.
    SleepCommand
    Deals with the command allowing the user to fall asleep.
    TakeCommand
    Deals with commands that pick up an object.
    UnknownCommand
    Deals with illegal commands.
    UnlockCommand
    Deals with the user's attempt to open a locked door.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    IllegalCommandException
    This exception is thrown if a user enters an illegal command.
    IllegalDungeonFormatException
    This exception is thrown if the bork file does not follow the proper format.
    IllegalSaveFormatException
    This exception is thrown if the save file does not follow the proper format.
    NoExitException
    This Exception is thrown when there are no more exits to read from a file.
    NoItemException
    This exception is thrown if a room, inventory or bork file contains no more items.
    NoRoomException
    This Exception is thrown when there are no more rooms to read from a file.
